                                            <h3 class="card-title fw-bold text-dark fs-3">Abstract Summary</h3>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="card-body p-4">
                                            <p class="text-secondary lh-lg m-0" style="text-align: justify; font-size: 1.05rem;">
                                                This research proposal outlines a comprehensive security evaluation of public and private key infrastructure deployed across modern IoT smart home frameworks. By analyzing potential edge execution nodes, the study aims to identify cryptographic latency trade-offs alongside physical and data-driven security configurations. The experimental design relies entirely on simulated machine states and open-source protocol packages. Metrics track data handling under localized stressors while providing automated script validations for device posture checks.
